{ The most precise, but of course, taking on d6 works too. } 11... exf4 12.
Nxd6+ cxd6 13. Bxf4
{ White is pretty much winning here. Just take a look at Black's pieces.   Conclusion: The Dark Knight Gambit is a must-know gambit for all the Fried Liver fans out there since it’s recommended by the ever-popular IM Levy Rozman a.k.a GothamChess. However, once you take on f7 with the bishop, the key idea is to play the quiet central push @@StartFEN@@r1bq1b1r/ppppkBpp/2n5/4p1N1/4n3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNBQK2R w KQ - 1 6@@EndFEN@@  6.d4!  It turns out that Black can’t take  on g5 due to a skewer and White gets a big attack. Sorry, GothamChess fans, you won’t last beyond move 15 in this one! }
