5... Nb4
{ Black's best move but a very difficult one to play without any knowledge. Interesting that both Carlsen & Nakamura didn't play this move. Perhaps, they should buy my course?! The idea of the ...Nb4 jump is to trade the d5-knight as quickly as possible with ...Nbxd5!   5...Nxe4  is playable but risky, as both  6.Bd3  and  6.Qe2  give White some initiative.   5...Nxd5?  is exactly what White is hoping to see.  6.exd5  Nb4  7.Bc4⩲  , with a clear  edge for White as the b4-knight is a bit stranded and the d4-pawn is also hit. }
