[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d6
{ This is the Philidor opening, a rare guest at tournament practice due to its passive nature. }
3. d4 f5
{ A dubious gambit, invented by famous French 18th-century player François-André Danican Philidor. He famously said, "Pawns are the Soul of chess." }
4. Bc4
{ A rare move, seen only in a few GM games! But I believe Black is facing serious issues due to the weak a2-g8 diagonal. }
4... exd4 { The most common move in the database. } 5. O-O
{ A simple move and Black's position is completely hopeless! White's rook enters the game. Let's look at some possible lines. }
5... fxe4 { This is a fun one to face! } 6. Nxd4 Nf6 7. Nc3
{ White develops and puts pressure on the e4-pawn. } 7... c6
{ 7...d5  8.Nxd5  Nxd5  9.Qh5++- } 8. Nxe4
{ A nice way to blow open the position! } 8... Nxe4 9. Re1 d5 10. Qh5+
{ The star move; Black is lost now. } 10... Kd7 { 10...g6  11.Qe5+ } 11. Rxe4
{ A fun sacrifice! White removes the last developed piece. } 11... dxe4 12. Bg5
{ White is totally crushing here. Let me share with you a fun line:  12...Be7  13.Ne6  Qe8  14.Rd1+  Bd6  15.Rxd6+!  Kxd6  16.Qd1+!  Not an easy move, but it leads to mate!  16...Ke5  17.Qd4+  Kf5  18.Qc5+  Kg6  @@StartBracket@@  18...Kg4  19.Be2#  @@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@rnb1q2r/pp4pp/2p1N1k1/2Q3B1/2B1p3/8/PPP2PPP/6K1 w - - 6 19@@EndFEN@@  19.Nf4#  . What a beautiful checkmate! }
