7. Bd2 c5 { White's strong center is collapsing. } 8. Nxe4
{ This was played by the strong Russian GM Andreikin vs. Kramnik back in 2010. }
8... dxe4 9. Bxb4 { This natural move actually helps Black! } 9... cxb4 10. Ng1
{ A sad decision, but where else can the knight go?  10.Nd2  drops the key central pawn:  10...Qxd4∓  . }
10... O-O
{ With a nice edge for Black as in the game Andreikin-Kramnik, Moscow 2010. White's kingside pieces are still on their initial squares while Black has already castled! }
