{ The Vienna Gambit is quite a dangerous gambit for Black if we take the pawn. I used to play this gambit for White as a kid and always loved it when Black took on f4 or just defended the pawn with  3...d6  as most club players do.   However, I will show you an idea based on central counterplay:  3...d5!  White players hate facing this countergambit, as Black gets fast central play. Please note that the popular YouTuber IM Levy Rozman a.k.a Gothamchess also loves the Vienna Gambit for White and recommends it in his videos. So, you have to be well-prepared here as Black! }
3... d5
{ The best and most direct approach. Always fight for the center!  3...exf4?  4.e5!  , with a big initiative for White. Also, @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pppp1ppp/5n2/4p3/4PP2/2N5/PPPP2PP/R1BQKBNR b KQkq f3 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3...d6?!  is too passive, and after  4.Nf3  , White gets a nice space advantage. }
4. fxe5 Nxe4 5. d3 { Another popular move to get rid of the strong knight. }
5... Nxc3 6. bxc3 d4
{ I like this idea to stop White from building a nice c3-d4-e5 pawn chain. } 7.
c4 { 7.cxd4?  Qxd4∓  and White will lose material. } 7... Bb4+ 8. Bd2 Nc6 9.
Nf3 Bg4 { Black has very easy play in this position. } *

