{ The Falkbeer Countergambit is named after the 19th-century Austrian master Ernst Falkbeer. Black doesn't care about winning a pawn, and instead, tries to blow open the center. The goal is rapid development above all!   2...exf4  3.Nf3  is the main line, but  3.Bc4!?  is also quite interesting and good. }
3. exd5
{ This is by far the most common move. White wants to draw Black's queen out to d5, where she'll be too vulnerable. }
