{ The best square for the bishop, inviting Ng5.  8...Bd6  9.Nd4!  is what we are trying to avoid. }
9. Ng5 O-O { Black happily sacs the pawn here. } 10. Nxe6 fxe6 11. Qxe6+
{ 11.Bxc6  bxc6  12.Qxe6+  Kh8  13.O-O  Qb6+  14.Kh1  Rae8  , with a big attack for Black. White is playing down a bishop and a rook! }
11... Kh8 { Believe it or not, White is already losing here. } 12. Bxc6 Qb6
{ A difficult move to see from a distance! White has no defense against ...Rae8 and winning on the e-file. }
13. Ne2 bxc6
{ With ...Rae8 next, Black will have a winning attack. White is basically playing down two rooks and a bishop now. }
