6... Bb4
{ This simple developing move is my antidote against most tries by White. We pin the knight and develop the bishop. }
7. Bd3
{ This was essayed by the young Greek GM Theodorou in 2022, but I believe Black is better. }
7... d6 { A rare move that was only seen in one game back in 2006. } 8. Rc1
{ 8.O-O  Bxc3  9.bxc3  e5!⩱  is the point behind the earlier ...d6. } 8... e5
{ My improvement over the DB game. } 9. Bg3 Be6 10. O-O Bxc3 11. Rxc3 f6
{ Black builds a stronghold on the kingside, totally shutting off the g3-bishop from the game. }
12. Nd2 Nge7 13. f4 O-O
{ Black is clearly better and White has no compensation for the pawn. } *

