[White "19) Sicilian Wing Gambit"]
[Black "Sicilian Wing Gambit 2.b4 cxb4 3.d4"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. b4
{ This is the Sicilian Wing Gambit, popular mostly at club level. Ginger GM Simon Williams recommends it as a sharp weapon against the Sicilian, so you have to be ready! }
2... cxb4 { We take the pawn and accept the challenge! } 3. d4
{ White immediately seizes the control over the center. } 3... d5
{ A timely strike! We can't allow White to have the center all to themselves. }
4. e5
{ White establishes a French-like pawn chain. But this is a bad French for White! Not only is Black up a pawn, but we can easily develop the bishop to f5, turning the game into a good Caro-Kann!   4.exd5  Nf6  , I prefer to take  the d5-pawn with the knight. This position is easy to play, as Black has an easy game. }
4... Bf5 { White is struggling to prove any compensation here. } 5. a3 Qa5 6.
Bd2 e6
{ Black is comfortably better. We will develop with ...Nc6 and eventually get the kingside out. White is facing an annoying pin, as the a1-rook is unprotected. }
*

