{ This move is less common than the popular  3...d5  , but I prefer to fight for the center with simple moves. Black activates  the bishop and protects the b4-pawn. }
4. Nf3 Nc6
{ The game now resembles a 1.e4 e5 opening but with a nice extra pawn for Black on b4. }
5. Bb2 Qb6
{ I like this rare move with only 9 games in the DB. Black sets up a cool trap! }
6. Bd3 { White's best, but it's an awkward move to make for a human. } 6... d6
7. O-O Nf6 8. axb4 Nxb4 9. Bc4
{ One correspondence game went like this, but Black is still better. } 9... Be7
10. d3 O-O 11. Ba3 Bg4 12. Nbd2 Nc6
{ As in the game Bobel-Glukhovtsev, ICCF email 2013, White doesn't have full compensation for the pawn. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "19) Sicilian Wing Gambit"]
[Black "Sicilian Wing Gambit 2.b4 cxb4 3.a3 e5 4.Nf3 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. b4
{ This is the Sicilian Wing Gambit, popular mostly at club level. Ginger GM Simon Williams recommends it as a sharp weapon against the Sicilian, so you have to be ready! }
2... cxb4 { We take the pawn and accept the challenge! } 3. a3
{ This is the most popular move, White offers this trade to activate the pieces. }
3... e5
{ This move is less common than the popular  3...d5  , but I prefer to fight for the center with simple moves. Black activates  the bishop and protects the b4-pawn. }
4. Nf3 Nc6
{ The game now resembles a 1.e4 e5 opening but with a nice extra pawn for Black on b4. }
5. Bb2 Qb6
{ I like this rare move with only 9 games in the DB. Black sets up a cool trap! }
6. Nxe5
{ White falls for the trap. Taking the e5-pawn with the bishop first is even worse, as after  6.Bxe5??  Nxe5  7.Nxe5  Qd4  , White is losing material. }
6... bxa3 7. Bc3 a2 { Luring the rook onto a weak square. } 8. Rxa2 Nxe5 9.
Bxe5 Qe6
{ The point behind the early ...Qb6 move. Faced with this double attack, White will lose material. }
10. Ra5 b6 11. Rd5
{ White's rook is performing defensive miracles, but they will lose the e4-pawn anyway. }
11... f6
{ The simplest.  11...Bb7  is good too, for example  12.Bc4  b5  13.Bb3  Bxd5  14.Bxd5  Qxe5  15.Bxa8  Nf6∓  . }
12. Bb2 Qxe4+ 13. Qe2 Qxe2+ 14. Bxe2 Bb7
{ Black will win another pawn, with a winning endgame. } *

