[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. b4
{ This is the Sicilian Wing Gambit, popular mostly at club level. Ginger GM Simon Williams recommends it as a sharp weapon against the Sicilian, so you have to be ready! }
2... cxb4 { We take the pawn and accept the challenge! } 3. a3
{ This is the most popular move, White offers this trade to activate the pieces. }
3... e5
{ This move is less common than the popular  3...d5  , but I prefer to fight for the center with simple moves. Black activates  the bishop and protects the b4-pawn. }
4. Nf3 Nc6
{ The game now resembles a 1.e4 e5 opening but with a nice extra pawn for Black on b4. }
5. Bc4 Nf6
{ The game looks a bit like the Two Knights Defense, but Black has the better version due to the extra b4-pawn. }
6. Ng5 { The Fried Liver Attack?! } 6... d5 { Black is ready! } 7. exd5 b5
{ Let's set the entire board on fire! } 8. Ba2 Nd4
{ Always choose active squares for your pieces! } 9. c3 b3
{ Making use of the extra b4-pawn; did you remember it used to be your c7-pawn? }
10. Bxb3 Nxb3 11. Qxb3 Qxd5 12. Qxd5 Nxd5
{ The dust has settled. White was able to get the pawn back, but Black's bishop pair will dominate the board as in Tuma-Bures, Ostrava 2018. }
