[White "20) French Wing Gambit"]
[Black "French Wing Gambit 4.b4 cxb4 5.a3 Qa5 6.Bb2 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. Nf3
{ White typically starts with this move to set up the French Wing Gambit, as they want to preserve the d-pawn. }
2... d5 3. e5 c5 4. b4
{ This is the idea behind the gambit. White wants to sacrifice the b-pawn in order to play d4 later and dominate the center. This is quite a dangerous gambit, as Black will be lacking central control for many moves. }
4... cxb4
{ The most principled reply! But accurate play is required from Black. } 5. a3
{ This is a bit more popular than an immediate  5.d4  . The point is that White wants to  achieve the c3-d4-e5 pawn chain if Black takes on a3. The other bonus is that sometimes White wants to trade the dark-squared bishop with Bxa3 next. }
5... Qa5
{ I recommend this rare move with the idea to stop White from building the c3-d4-e5 pawn chain, played by Firouzja in 2020. Now White can't take on b4, as the a1-rook is unprotected.   5...Nc6  6.axb4  Bxb4  7.c3  Be7  8.d4  is what White is aiming for, while @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pp3ppp/4p3/3pP3/1p6/P4N2/2PP1PPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 0 5@@EndFEN@@  5...bxa3  6.d4  Nc6  7.c3  is the point of White's plan. }
6. Bb2
{ The most logical move. White develops the bishop and protects the a1-rook. Now they want to take on b4. }
6... Nc6
{ Black develops the knight to a natural square and gets ready for axb4. } 7.
Bd3 { White aims for a fast development in this line. } 7... Qc7
{ The queen did her job of stopping the annoying c3-d4-e5 pawn chain and Black resumes the typical French development. The queen is quite safe on c7. }
8. O-O Bd7 9. Re1 Nh6
{ A natural novelty where the knight aims to jump to f5 or g4 without blocking the bishop. }
10. h3 Be7 11. g4 { Trying to restrict the knight, but it's not a good idea! }
11... O-O 12. Kg2 f5
{ A cool idea to remember, but other moves such as ...a5 or ...f6 are good as well. Black is winning in all lines! }
13. g5 { 13.gxf5  Nxf5  and White's king is too exposed. } 13... Nf7 14. h4 d4
{ The e5-pawn is doomed. } *

