{ Our pawn is wreaking havoc in White's camp. There's no good way to capture it, so White usually leaves it alone for now. }
9. Kf1
{ White now aims to take the pawn with the bishop, leaving the e1-square for the rook. }
9... Nc6
{ Now, it's development above all. Black doesn't mind losing the d2-pawn. } 10.
Bxd2 Nd4 { White's queen is getting harassed. } 11. Qa4+ Bd7 12. Qa5 Qb4 13.
Re1+ Be6 14. Qxc7
{ 14.Qxb4  Bxb4  , we are always happy to trade queens since Black has an extra pawn. White gets the pawn back, but now it's Black who gets the development edge. }
14... Be7 { 14...Bd6?  15.Nb5! } 15. Bxe6 Nxe6 16. Qe5 Qxb2
{ Black is still a pawn up and will castle next, while White's king is stuck on f1. }
