[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5
{ This is the Advance Variation of the French Defense. White makes their aggressive intention clear by creating a powerful pawn chain. }
3... c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Qb6 6. Bd3
{ This aggressive line is named after a British chess player, Stuart Milner-Barry, who among other things was a code breaker during WWII! }
