{ The simple refutation, don't take the pawn on d3!  4...exd3  5.Bxd3  h6??  is what White had in mind, and now  6.Nxf7!  Kxf7  7.Bg6+  , when Black loses the queen:  7...Kxg6  8.Qxd8+-  . }
5. Be2 { This just allows more trades. } 5... Bxe2 6. Qxe2 exd3 7. cxd3 e6 8.
O-O Nc6
{ White is down a pawn and has a terrible weakness on d3. Black is rock solid and will easily convert the material advantage. }
