{ This is the most difficult move to remember! Believe it or not, this quiet pawn move is the best line! It's important to take away the ...Bb4+ option from Black.   4.Nf3  Bb4+  @@StartBracket@@  4...d6!?  5.exd6  Bxd6  ,  hoping for a natural g3 move, which loses the game on the spot!  6.g3?  Nxf2!  7.Kxf2  Bxg3+-+  and White drops the queen.@@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/pppp1ppp/8/4P3/1bP1n3/5N2/PP2PPPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 3 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Nbd2  Nc6  is what Black wants. Eventually, White will drop  the e5-pawn. }
4... d6
{ Black's most popular move. The internet blitz specialist IM Yaacov Norowitz from NYC @@StartBracket@@YaakovN@@EndBracket@@ plays this line all the time, even against GMs. }
5. Qc2
{ This is quite a rare move but a very strong idea. Black has to decide what to do with the e4-knight. }
5... d5
{ This has been played in several master games, but White is better with pretty much any natural move. }
6. e3 Bf5 7. Nc3 Ng3 8. e4
{ The e4 tactic still works even with the pawn on d5! } 8... Nxe4
{ 8...Nxh1  9.exf5+- } 9. Bd3 { The pressure on the e4-knight is too much. }
9... Nd7 10. cxd5 Nxc3 11. Bxf5 Nxd5 12. Nf3
{ White will castle next and will dominate with two bishops on the open board. }
