{ Black's best move, giving White several options on which piece to capture.  6...Nd6  instead is less precise, as it allows White to hope for compensation after  7.Bf4  e6  8.O-O-O  . }
7. bxc3 { White's best, but not an easy decision since it doubles the pawns. }
7... e6
{ Black plays a development move, sacrificing the b7-pawn for initiative! } 8.
Qxb7
{ White takes the pawn and accepts the challenge. Now, Black is the one playing in gambit style and goes for rapid development and piece play. }
