O-O { 12...Qc7  is fine as well. } 13. O-O Qc7
{ With a nice edge for Black due to White's ruined pawn structure. The only game in the database continued  14.Qd3  Rb3  15.Bd2  Ndf6  16.Ne5  Bf5-+  and White is close to losing due to the many pins and threats as in the game Kaytazki-Tsenkov, ICCF email 2018.   Conclusion: Grob's Attack is an unsound gambit that should be refuted at once! Remember that the key idea is to allow White to win the b7-pawn and develop quickly. Oftentimes, White will either get the queen trapped or lose too many tempi trying to save it. As always with these unsound gambits, development is above all! }
